01</a>). <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript=
/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toJSON"><code>toJSON()</code></a> calls <cod=
e>toISOString()</code> and returns the result.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Refe=
rence/Global_Objects/Date/toString"><code>toString()</code></a> returns a s=
tring in the format <code>Thu Jan 01 1970 00:00:00 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Un=
iversal Time)</code>, while <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/=
docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toDateString"><code>toDat=
eString()</code></a> and <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/doc=
s/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toTimeString"><code>toTimeSt=
ring()</code></a> return the date and time parts of the string, respectivel=
y. <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Refer=
ence/Global_Objects/Date/Symbol.toPrimitive"><code>[Symbol.toPrimitive]()</=
code></a> (when passed <code>"string"</code> or <code>"default"</code>) cal=
ls <code>toString()</code> and returns the result.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Refe=
rence/Global_Objects/Date/toUTCString"><code>toUTCString()</code></a> retur=
ns a string in the format <code>Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT</code> (gener=
alized <a href=3D"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231" class=3D"e=
xternal" target=3D"_blank">RFC 7231</a>).</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Refe=
rence/Global_Objects/Date/toLocaleDateString"><code>toLocaleDateString()</c=
ode></a>, <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScrip=
t/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toLocaleTimeString"><code>toLocaleTimeStrin=
g()</code></a>, and <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web=
/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/toLocaleString"><code>toLocaleStr=
ing()</code></a> use locale-specific date and time formats, usually provide=
d by the <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript=
/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl"><code>Intl</code></a> API.</li>
</ul>
<p>See the <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScri=
pt/Reference/Global_Objects/Date#formats_of_tostring_method_return_values">=
Formats of <code>toString</code> method return values</a> section for examp=
les.</p>
  </section><section class=3D"content-section" aria-labelledby=3D"construct=
